Map created for the UV mapping contest September 2008.

In Uvalno village, where I live, is villa next to my house. Fortunately it is my friend's villa, so he agreed with reconstruction his house to CSS map (His name is Ulicny  so I named map after him "Ulicni"). He provided  groundplans and allowed me to take some panorama photos. I worked on this almost 3 months.

This is my second reconstruction project of Uvalno village, so it is not playable because of low fps (there are only 3 player start of each side).

I wanted participate on Realistic Mapping Contest with villa, but I decided to post uvalno_kostel to the contest.

I remade this map to playable hostage rescue version,

If you like this one, check all of my maps here
This map or its parts is also used in my singleplayer mod

Have a fun
Dinus Saurus

This is a training map that was made for my clan upon request.  There are four areas of the map:

1st: A basic area for knifing
2nd: A maze intended for using sound and little light to find opponents.
3rd: A balancing platform for more knife practice.
4th: The large building which is intended for one on one gun fights.  There are buyzones in the building (Counter-Terrorists to the left, Terrorists to the right).

There are only two spawns due to the style and layout of the map, so is intended for improving skills for one on one combat.

The map has HDR lighting available as well and a 3d skybox for better scenery.

Well I hope you enjoy the map.

This is "sequel" to trap_catacombs. It's a tighter and smaller version of a traps map which includes even more interesting traps and play on triggers.

The classic "floortrap" traps are still in, and there are some special ones, such as the water trap, a slowly water filled room, the panic button, the yellow corridor, and so on.

This is a definitely good map to add to any fun/custom maps server.

The trap maps, as I call them, are maps where two teams are thrown into a maze-like map filled with concealed traps.

trap_catacombs is a dark and scary map where players need to eliminate their opposing team before the traps do. There are about 30 different traps in the map, and a scary theme to it. If you like new ideas and interesting concepts, this map is for you!
I've worked on it for quite a while and finally made a nice finished product. Even a few servers have that map in their lists! This is a great addition to any custom-map server. I've had a lot of feedback and took ideas given to me by other players to add more traps!

Don't judge this map by the screenshots, you'll need to play it to really judge it!
